File: AFP Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Abuja - Nigeria's government on Wednesday said another Chibok girl was free, having escaped from Boko Haram Islamists more than three years after she was kidnapped with more than 200 classmates. Presidency spokesperson Femi Adesina said Vice President Yemi Osinbajo informed ministers at a cabinet meeting.She was "found by the Nigerian troops while she was escaping", added government aide Bashir Ahmad. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.